@node Generic Function @code{convert}
@chapter Generic Function @code{convert}

The @code{convert} generic function provides convenient conversions between many FSet types.  It is
called with the first argument @var{to-type} being a symbol --- normally a quoted constant --- that
specifies the target type of the conversion, and the second argument being the collection to be
converted.  (This is the opposite order from @code{cl:coerce}.)  Many methods have additional
keyword parameters to further specify details of the conversion.

When @code{to-type} is one of the abstract types -- @code{set}, @code{bag}, @code{map} etc. -- the
only guarantee is that @code{convert} will return an instance of the requested type.  The choices of
implementation and organization are up to FSet, and there's no option to request a specific
organization.  In contrast, when @code{to-type} is one of the concrete types -- @code{wb-set},
@code{ch-set}, @code{wb-map}, etc. -- the @code{convert} method accepts keyword arguments specifying
the organization (e.g.  @code{compare-fn-name}), and guarantees to return a collection of that type
and organization; including the case where no organization is specified, in which @code{convert} is
guaranteed to return a collection of the default organization (the one using @code{fset:compare}).

